title: 820-3115 green light no power
message:
board wont turn on and had very noticeable water damage. replaced whatever was badly damaged and retraced some areas. i get a green light on charger.

pp3v3_s4=.600v

something is pulling s4 down correct?

tried comparing the board with a known good but could not find any obvious differences besides pp3v3_s4 being low.

what should i look for?

title: 820-3115 green light no power
message: Need to know is PPBUS present, 3v3_S5? Voltage on C1802/03, crap under SMC likely.

title: 820-3115 green light no power
message:
ppbus is present
3v3_s5 is present
5v_s5 is present
c1802 is 3.0v

i removed smc and area looks clean

title: 820-3115 green light no power
message: Clock chip replaced if liquid was there? Any sign of power cycling?

title: 820-3115 green light no power
message:

as far as power cycling no

title: 820-3115 green light no power
message: Could be so many things now. Was there corrosion around the PCH? Checked all rails for shorts? What SMC did you put back on?
